## Setup UFS Coastal App

### Prerequisites

Spack-stack environment needs to be installed.
A spack binary mirror exists for this deployment to make this easier and faster.
See Cloud-Sandbox/scripts/ufs-setup-instance.sh
spack-stack should work on an older currently deployed head node alongside the regular spack.
UFS uses spack-stack.

### Scripts

setup.sh - Clone the gitHub repository and build the ROMS App.
Default location: /save/ec2-user/ufs-weather-model

get_input_data.sh - Dowload the ROMS Irene and SCHISM Ike test case inputs
Default location: /com/ufs-weather-model/RT/NEMSfv3gfs/input-data-20250507

### How To Run

Currently the Irene ROMS regression test has been tested.
Ike SCHISM tests should be easy to add at this point.

The run will launch a single node to build and run the preconfigured test(s).

Modify the cluster/configs for your deployment (see cluster/configs/IOOS/ufs.rt).

Set non-default directories in:  job/jobs/UFS/ufs.irene

Launch the job:
nohup workflows/workflow_main.py cluster/configs/IOOS/ufs.rt job/jobs/UFS/ufs.irene > & ufs.out &

Cloudflow workflow uses cloudflow/workflow/ufs_launcher.sh to call the rt.sh script in the UFS /save/ec2-user/ufs-weather-model/tests.
See ufs_launcher.sh for additional options.

